Based on this property, we design a non-Hermitian acoustic flat lens to focus on the acoustic plane wave. Figure 7(a) shows the schematic diagram of the flat lens, which offers more possibilities for controlling the geometric freedom of metamaterials. The hyperboloidal phase profile along the y direction is used to realize acoustic point focusing at a distance f from the structure. For a given focal length f, the positions of phase shift ϕ(y) in the y direction must satisfy the equation:5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
